---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'

const title = 'Why is 530A Model free?'
const description =
  '530A Model is a public-good passion project: no ads, no upsells, no email capture, no data sold. Here’s why it exists and how it stays free.'
---

<Base title={title} description={description} path="/why-free">
  <section style="padding: 2rem 0 0;">
    <h1>Why is this free?</h1>
    <p>
      Because the question it answers shouldn't cost anything. Millions of families are hearing
      about 530A accounts for the first time and deserve a fast, honest answer to “what could this
      actually be worth for my kid?” — without handing over an email address, sitting through a
      sales pitch, or trusting a black box.
    </p>
    <h2>No monetization. Really.</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No ads</strong>, no affiliate links, no sponsored funds.</li>
      <li><strong>No accounts or email capture</strong> — there is nothing to sign up for.</li>
      <li><strong>No data collection</strong> — calculations run entirely in your browser.</li>
      <li><strong>Open source</strong> — the math is public and independently tested.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>How it stays free</h2>
    <p>
      The site is built so that serving one visitor or a million costs nearly the same: static
      pages on a CDN, with all calculation done on your device. Hosting costs are a few dollars a
      month, paid personally as a public-good project.
    </p>
    <p>
      If it helped you, share it with another parent. That's the whole business model.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
